^-{      No one gets rich betting on 50-50 propositions      }
^-|fp||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|A finesse is a maneuver to win a trick with a card that is not an obvious winner. Many players love to finesse. It's usually simple and supplies immediate gratification – when it works. However, experts don't like to finesse. Why? Finesses lose half the time, and no one gets rich betting on 50-50 propositions. Of course, that doesn't mean you should never finesse. Finessing will always be an important part of bridge.

For each of the following 15 deals, I will explain the initial thinking to help you decide the key question – To Finesse or Not To Finesse.|
