NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|It is often right to cover an honor with an honor. But experts always count out the hand. On this hand, South opened a weak 2, which means he has 6, and there are 5 spades in dummy. So there are only 2 spades out and West has them both. Therefore, partner is void. So covering will merely eliminate the guess declarer has, as to whether to play you for @SKx or play for a 1-1 break. Covering can never gain you a trick. |
